{\f0\fs32 2. FEATURE: SEGMENT EDITING & EMPTY TEXT HANDLING}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Commits: 526b964, 3c8c1cf, 93e7e04, ebcf8fc\line Date: March 21, 2026 13:45\u821314:00\line Files: }{\f2\fs20\cf6 src/components/viewer/TranscriptText.tsx}
\par\par

{\f0\fs24 2.1 What Was Changed}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 Four changes to the transcript segment editing UI in }{\f2\fs20 TranscriptText.tsx}{\f1\fs22 :}
\par\par
{\f0\fs22 A. Empty text segments auto-enter edit mode.}{\f1\fs22  Previously, when a new empty segment was added to the transcript, the user had to click on it to start typing. Now, segments with empty text and IDs starting with }{\f2\fs20 'new-'}{\f1\fs22  automatically enter edit mode on render.}
\par\par
{\f2\fs18 // Before:\line const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(false);\line\line // After:\line const isNewEmpty = segment.text === '' && segment.id.startsWith('new-');\line const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(isNewEmpty);}
\par\par
{\f0\fs22 B. Save handler allows empty text.}{\f1\fs22  The save handler previously required }{\f2\fs20 editValue.trim()}{\f1\fs22  to be truthy (non-empty) before saving. This prevented users from clearing a segment's text. Changed to check }{\f2\fs20 editValue.trim() !== segment.text}{\f1\fs22  instead, allowing saves of empty strings and deletions.}
\par\par
{\f2\fs18 // Before:\line if (editValue.trim() && editValue.trim() !== segment.text)\line\line // After:\line if (editValue.trim() !== segment.text)}
\par\par
{\f0\fs22 C. Empty text placeholder display.}{\f1\fs22  Segments with no text now show italic gray placeholder text "Click to add text..." instead of rendering as invisible empty space. The CSS class dynamically switches between normal text styling and placeholder styling based on whether }{\f2\fs20 segment.text}{\f1\fs22  is truthy.}
\par\par
{\f0\fs22 D. Type casting fix.}{\f1\fs22  Fixed a TypeScript error where editing a dialogue segment's properties passed incorrect types to the update handler.}
\par\par

{\f0\fs24 2.2 Why}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 Users needed to add new dialogue segments (e.g., when a speaker's line was missing from the transcript) and immediately start typing. The previous behavior required an extra click and couldn't handle empty segments without errors.}
\par\par

