\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Commits: 31eea63, ea852d7, 2373718\line Date: March 21, 2026 14:55\u821315:06\line New Files (6):\line }{\f2\fs20\cf6 server/checkAccess.ts\line server/routes/shares.ts\line src/components/sharing/ShareModal.tsx\line src/contexts/SharedContext.tsx\line src/hooks/useShared.ts\line src/types/transcript.ts}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Modified Files (9):\line }{\f2\fs20\cf6 server/index.ts, server/routes/annotations.ts, server/routes/folders.ts,\line server/routes/transcripts.ts, src/App.tsx, src/components/layout/Sidebar.tsx,\line src/components/viewer/MetadataEditor.tsx, src/components/viewer/TranscriptText.tsx,\line src/components/viewer/TranscriptToolbar.tsx, src/contexts/TranscriptContext.tsx,\line src/pages/TranscriptViewerPage.tsx, src/utils/api.ts}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Lines Added: ~1,481}
\par\par

{\f0\fs24 3.1 What Was Changed}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 A complete coworking and sharing system was implemented, allowing users to share individual transcripts or entire folders with other users at different permission levels (view or edit).}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.1 Backend: Access Control System (}{\f2\fs20 server/checkAccess.ts}{\f0\fs22 )}
\par
{\f1\fs22 A centralized access control function }{\f2\fs20 checkAccess(userId, resourceType, resourceId)}{\f1\fs22  was created. It checks:}
{\f2\fs18 \line 1. Is the user the owner of the resource? -> Full access\line 2. Does a share record exist granting this user access? -> Permission-based access\line 3. For transcripts in a shared folder: does a folder-level share exist? -> Inherited access\line\line Returns: \{ allowed: boolean, permission: 'owner' | 'edit' | 'view' | null \}}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.2 Backend: Share Routes (}{\f2\fs20 server/routes/shares.ts}{\f0\fs22 , 401 lines)}
\par
{\f1\fs22 A full REST API for sharing:}
{\f2\fs18 \line POST   /api/shares              Create a share (email, resourceType, resourceId, permission)\line GET    /api/shares/by-resource   List shares for a specific resource\line GET    /api/shares/shared-with-me  List all resources shared with the current user\line PATCH  /api/shares/:id            Update share permission\line DELETE /api/shares/:id            Revoke a share (soft delete via revoked_at)\line\line Security features:\line - Only the resource owner can create/modify/revoke shares\line - Email-based sharing: if the target email doesn't have an account, the share\line   silently succeeds (no information disclosure about user existence)\line - Self-sharing is rejected\line - Duplicate shares are detected and updated rather than duplicated\line - Revoked shares can be re-activated with a new permission level}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.3 Backend: Transcript Route Security Hardening}
\par
{\f1\fs22 The }{\f2\fs20 server/routes/transcripts.ts}{\f1\fs22  file was significantly modified (~148 line changes) to integrate access control checks into every endpoint:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - GET /api/transcripts/:id       Now checks checkAccess() before returning data\line - PUT /api/transcripts/:id       Only allows edits if permission is 'owner' or 'edit'\line - DELETE /api/transcripts/:id    Only allows deletion by owner\line - PUT /api/transcripts/:id/segments  Edit-permission required for segment saves\line - Annotation routes: access-controlled}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.4 Frontend: ShareModal Component (}{\f2\fs20 src/components/sharing/ShareModal.tsx}{\f0\fs22 , 180 lines)}
\par
{\f1\fs22 A modal dialog for managing shares:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Email input to share with a user\line - Permission dropdown (View / Edit)\line - List of current shares with permission badges\line - Revoke button for each share\line - Integrated into TranscriptToolbar via a "Share" button}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.5 Frontend: Shared Context & Sidebar}
\par
{\f1\fs22 A }{\f2\fs20 SharedContext}{\f1\fs22  (}{\f2\fs20 src/contexts/SharedContext.tsx}{\f1\fs22 ) provides a }{\f2\fs20 useShared()}{\f1\fs22  hook that fetches and caches }{\f2\fs20 /api/shares/shared-with-me}{\f1\fs22 . The sidebar (}{\f2\fs20 Sidebar.tsx}{\f1\fs22 ) was modified to show a "Shared with Me" section listing transcripts and folders shared by other users, with visual indicators for permission level (view/edit badge).}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.6 Frontend: Permission-Aware UI}
\par
{\f1\fs22 Multiple components were updated to respect permissions:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - TranscriptToolbar: Share button visible only to owners\line - TranscriptText: Edit controls hidden for view-only users\line - MetadataEditor: Read-only mode for view-only users\line - TranscriptViewerPage: Permission state threaded through all child components}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 3.1.7 Auto-Save for Notes and Bookmarks}
\par
{\f1\fs22 Notes and bookmarks are now automatically saved when the user modifies them, instead of requiring a manual save action. This was implemented alongside the sharing feature to ensure shared collaborators see real-time updates.}
\par\par

