{\f0\fs22 4.1.3 Automatic Browser-Playable Audio Conversion (12f1738)}
\par
{\f1\fs22 Added a }{\f2\fs20 convertToBrowserPlayable()}{\f1\fs22  function to the transcription pipeline in }{\f2\fs20 server/transcription.ts}{\f1\fs22 :}
\par\par
{\f2\fs18 BROWSER_PLAYABLE_FORMATS = ['.mp3', '.wav', '.ogg', '.m4a', '.aac', '.flac', '.webm', '.mp4', '.oga']\line\line If the source file is NOT in a browser-playable format:\line 1. Convert to MP3 at 44.1kHz stereo 128kbps via ffmpeg\line 2. Upload the MP3 to S3 with the same key but .mp3 extension\line 3. Update the transcript's file_url in the database to point to the MP3\line\line If the source file IS browser-playable: no conversion (return null)}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 This ensures that all transcripts have browser-playable audio URLs regardless of the original upload format. The conversion runs at the beginning of the pipeline, before Whisper processing, and is non-fatal (errors are caught and logged).}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 A }{\f2\fs20 /api/media/:key(*)}{\f1\fs22  endpoint was also added to }{\f2\fs20 server/index.ts}{\f1\fs22  to proxy S3 media files to the browser with appropriate content-type headers (54 line change). This allows the frontend audio player to stream audio directly from the server without CORS issues from S3.}
