{\f0\fs32 8. FEATURE: SYNCHRONIZED POP-OUT PRESENTER WINDOW}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Commit: ae276e2\line Date: March 22, 2026 02:30\line New Files (2):\line }{\f2\fs20\cf6 src/hooks/usePresentSync.ts (98 lines)\line src/pages/PresenterPopout.tsx (278 lines)}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Modified Files (5):\line }{\f2\fs20\cf6 src/App.tsx, src/components/viewer/TranscriptToolbar.tsx,\line src/pages/TranscriptViewerPage.tsx, src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx, replit.md}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22\cf6 Lines Added: ~1,333}
\par\par

{\f0\fs24 8.1 Architecture}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 This feature converts the presentation mode from a full-page navigation (leaving the transcript viewer) to a synced pop-out window (opens a new browser window while the main app stays open). The main app owns all audio/video playback and broadcasts state to the pop-out window via the BroadcastChannel API.}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 8.1.1 BroadcastChannel Sync Hook (}{\f2\fs20 src/hooks/usePresentSync.ts}{\f0\fs22 )}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 Two hooks for cross-window communication:}
\par\par
{\f0\fs20 }{\f2\fs18 usePresentBroadcaster(transcriptId)}{\f0\fs20  \u8212 used by the main app:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Opens a BroadcastChannel named 'mms-present-sync'\line - broadcast(state): sends current playback state to all listeners\line - onCommand(handler): registers a handler for commands from the pop-out\line - Responds to 'request_state' handshake from pop-out on mount\line\line State broadcast payload (PresentState):\line   transcriptId, currentTime, isPlaying, playbackRate, duration,\line   filename, mediaType, mediaUrl, segments[]}
\par\par
{\f0\fs20 }{\f2\fs18 usePresentReceiver(transcriptId)}{\f0\fs20  \u8212 used by the pop-out window:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Opens a BroadcastChannel on the same name\line - Receives state updates, exposes state as React state\line - sendCommand(cmd): sends commands back to the main app\line - On mount: sends 'request_state' handshake to get initial state\line\line Commands (PresentCommand):\line   play, pause, toggle, seek, skip, rate, request_state}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 8.1.2 Presenter Pop-Out Page (}{\f2\fs20 src/pages/PresenterPopout.tsx}{\f0\fs22 , 278 lines)}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 A unified pop-out window that handles both audio and video transcripts:}
\par\par
{\f0\fs20 Audio Mode:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Full-screen scrolling transcript with active segment highlighting\line - Large, readable text optimized for courtroom/deposition display\line - Progress bar at the top\line - Play/pause control button\line - Click-to-seek on any segment (sends seek command to main app)}
\par\par
{\f0\fs20 Video Mode:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Split layout: video player at top, transcript scroll below\line - Video element syncs to main app's playback state (time, play/pause, rate)\line - Resizable video area with a drag handle (user can drag to resize video vs. text)\line - "Show/hide text" toggle to show video only\line - Click-to-seek on segments (seeks both video and main app)\line - Video height persisted as percentage of viewport}
\par\par
{\f0\fs20 Shared Features:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Light/dark theme: reads from localStorage ('mms-theme'), listens for\line   storage events so theme changes in the main app propagate to the pop-out\line - Active segment auto-scroll: smoothly scrolls the current segment into view\line - Window title set to transcript filename\line - Keyboard shortcuts: Space (play/pause)}
\par\par

{\f0\fs22 8.1.3 Main App Integration}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 }{\f2\fs20 TranscriptViewerPage.tsx}{\f1\fs22  was modified to:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - Call usePresentBroadcaster(id) to create the broadcast channel\line - Broadcast playback state on every audio player state change\line   (currentTime, isPlaying, playbackRate, duration updates)\line - Listen for commands from the pop-out and execute them\line   (play, pause, seek, skip, rate changes)\line - State broadcasts are scoped by transcript ID to prevent cross-talk\line   when multiple transcript tabs are open}
\par\par
{\f1\fs22 }{\f2\fs20 TranscriptToolbar.tsx}{\f1\fs22  was modified to:}
{\f2\fs18 \line - "Present" button now calls window.open() to open a pop-out window\line   at /app/presenter/\{id\} instead of navigating to a new page\line - Pop-out window size: 800x900 pixels, resizable}
